        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on GRW’s paper [<hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> (1843): 65–7; <hi rend="italic">Ann. &amp; Mag. Nat. Hist.</hi> 12 (1843): 399–412]. CD says by "link" between any two groups he never understood a half-way link, merely one in a long series. Observes that one cannot have a simple species intermediate between two great families. Criticises GRW’s use of circles to represent groups, which leads to thinking that groups are of equal value.</p> 
        </abstract>
